segment.source: This topic for the IT professional describes the advanced security audit policy setting, Audit IPsec Main Mode, which determines whether the operating system generates events for the results of the Internet Key Exchange (IKE) protocol and Authenticated Internet Protocol (AuthIP) during Main Mode negotiations.
segment.target: This topic for the IT professional describes the advanced security audit policy setting, Audit IPsec Main Mode, which determines whether the operating system generates events for the results of the Internet Key Exchange (IKE) protocol and Authenticated Internet Protocol (AuthIP) during Main Mode negotiations.

segment.source: Audit IPsec Main Mode allows you to audit events generated by Internet Key Exchange protocol (IKE) and Authenticated Internet Protocol (AuthIP) during Main Mode negotiations.
segment.target: Audit IPsec Main Mode allows you to audit events generated by Internet Key Exchange protocol (IKE) and Authenticated Internet Protocol (AuthIP) during Main Mode negotiations.
